==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Operculated
<hw>O*per"cu*la`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>operculatus</ets>, p.
p. of <ets>operculare</ets> to furnish with a lid, fr.
<ets>operculum</ets> lid.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Closed by a lid or cover, as the capsules of the mosses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having an operculum, or an
apparatus for protecting the gills; -- said of shells and of
fishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Operculiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
